column5: Only had a few left where I bought mine.
I'm sure all those short staffed types will be out there, lol

I like it. I once saw a gag tape in a Florida tackle shop that was actually marked wrong just for measuring fish. 1 foot was about 10 actual inches if I recall. It would not be good if someone used it for construction by mistake. A guy marks 4' cuts it and the thing is 12" short, oops.
